About BRHacks

BRHacks is a full-day hackathon organized at the Bridgewater-Raritan High School in NJ. We seek to be a competitive event while making space for programming newcomers, as well as provide educational value through specialized workshops. Speeches from industry leaders and academia, as well as a focused theme of the medical industry ensure that we inspire sustainability for the future.

FAQ

Where is the Hackathon?
600 Garretson Road, Bridgewater, NJ, 08807
Where should I register?
Coming soon!
Is there a fee for participation?
No, everything (including food) is free, thanks to our wonderful sponsors.
What can I learn?
We have a variety of events rich with content. These events include topics from computer science, business, psychology, and more. You can check out our events below on our website.
Will there be food?
Yes! We will have snacks and drinks throughout the Hackathon. We will also serve lunch and dinner.
Who can attend?
Any high schooler is free to join regardless of where you are.
What prizes will there be?
To be decided, but they will be very well worth it!
Do I need a team?
You are not required to have a team. We will have opportunities for you during the competition to network and form your own teams at the Hackathon.
Can I participate if I am new to Hackathon?
Yes! We will have plenty of beginner-friendly events, workshops, and competitions for you to join.
What should I bring?
Bring your computer, charger, snacks, and any other electronics you may need.
When will the Hackathon be?
Fall of 2024
What time does registration start?
Registration starts at 9AM.
